  "summary": "After Miss Beatrix Lippincott leaves her shop assistant, Lily, to arrange linens, David Hunter enters Room 5 to meet a man identifying himself as Inok Jacobson (also referred to as Enock Yatton or Judd). David observes that the man appears worn-out and elusive. During a meeting involving whiskey, the man reveals that he knew David’s sister Rosalyn’s first husband, Robert André (also referred to as Robert Andorra), very well.\n\nThe man suggests that André did not actually die in Africa as believed, but instead faked his death to manipulate local natives and reappear under a new name. He implies that if André were to reappear, it would reveal that Rosalyn’s current marriage to Gordon-Claude is bigamous, potentially invalidating her inheritance and Gordon-Claude's prenuptial agreement. The man claims André is alive but in poor health and requires expensive medical treatment.\n\nDavid initially accuses the man of extortion, but the man threatens to go public with the information to the Claude family. To protect his sister and her status, David agrees to pay. After the man demands two million, David refuses, noting Rosalyn cannot touch her principal investment. The man lowers the demand to one million. David agrees to the payment on the condition that it be made in cash. He instructs the man to bring the money to Stagg on Tuesday night at nine o'clock. David leaves the room in a state of intense anger.",
